The coast is now clear for Senator Abdullahi Adamu, President Muhammadu Buhari favoured for the office of national chairman of the All Progressives Congress. The position is zoned to North Central. A letter signed by one of the aspirants, Senator George Akume on behalf of five others titled, dated March 25, 2022 and addressed to Chairman Subcommittee of the APC National Convention, Abubakar Badaru,  disclosed that they have all conceeded to Senator Adamu as Consensus candidate. Other aspirants who signed the letter were former Zamfara state governor, Abdul Aziz Yari, Senator Tanko Al-Makura, Alhaji Saliu Mustapha, Senator Sani Musa and Alhaji Mohammed Etsum Indication has also emerged that the office of national secretary zoned to South West will now be decided by voting by delegates. Details later… YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state… Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report… ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
